  "firstAcquaintance": "Forced by circumstances into massive debt, Roland donned a bunny girl outfit and started working as a waiter at a hotel.",
  "personality": "After putting on the bunny girl outfit, he displays the gentle attentiveness of a butler. He's also become even more of a pervert.",
  "like": "Older women, generous customers",
  "familiarData": "Accidentally fell into massive debt? Of course that's fake.\nRoland deliberately overspent as an excuse to carry out espionage work (the official reason) and hang out with older women (the real priority), smoothly arranging to stay and work off his debt.\nRoland puts his combat experience to good use: his movements are clean and efficient, and he can anticipate enemies' (customers') needs before they even speak, fulfilling their requests ahead of time. He single-handedly handles all the waitstaff duties, allowing him to work off his debt more efficiently. Of course, repaying the debt is just a side benefit -- the important thing is monopolizing the opportunity to serve older women.\n\nDon't underestimate the bunny girl outfit. This attire lets Roland unleash 100% of his assassination skills, silently subduing unruly customers. He also makes use of poses taught to him by older women to perform precision strikes on customers' wallets.\nWait, shouldn't an assassin wear something inconspicuous?\nNo, no, no -- wearing something flashy without being detected is the true mark of an assassin's skill.",
